Created an attachment (id=63432)
Generator change to generate the eStaticFeatureCount method.

Probably we should just get the generator to produce an eStaticFeatureCount that returns 0 in the root class impls.

Hi Ed,

I just looked at the patch, and I'm wondering about a potential problem: what if you have a subclass in another model that doesn't use reflective delegation? It would seem the eStaticFeatureCount() of 0 would be wrong then. Should you be generating another override in that case?

This problem would also be in 2.2, right?

Dave,

So far we've been telling people they need to provide their own base class (Root Extends Class in the GenModel) to make this pattern work so that wouldn't cover the case you describe; that's what Radu is doing now.  I'm not sure if the pattern would work for that case, but I can give it a try and for cases like that, we could generate a constant representing the number of non-dynamic features already provided by the non-reflective base class.

Created an attachment (id=63739)
A more general approach

This approach will allow a non-reflective base model to be extended and will generate the correct static feature count value.  I tested it with the school library example with both the case of the base being reflective and it not being reflective.
The fix to generate an eStaticFeatureCount is committed to CVS.
